        "TextSection": {
            "TextSectionType": "Definition",
            "Contents": "A rare overgrowth syndrome characterized by polyhydramnios pre- and postnatal macrosomia muscular hypotonia renal anomalies organomegaly abdominal distension cryptorchidism typical facial dysmorphism neurodevelopmental delay and high neonatal mortality. Individuals surviving infancy show a high risk of developing Wilms tumor."
        },
